      "id": "PopularPost184994",
      "post_content": "I think that land destruction should be a little slow down from Stone Rain to prevent some crazy deck type like permission and discard. Even worse you can always draw a card each turn (a new threat, a new spell to cast), but you can't recover from land destruction so easily. However I think that punish non-basic land should the way to go. The game can hinder those 300\u20ac/$ deck full of double land of some sort and give the budget (or new) player some tools to have a chance... Also a reason why the [Primeval Titan](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Primeval Titan) should read \"basic land\". Like the non-budget player weren't incentivated enough... in the same vein they could bring [Ruination](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ruination) back!  \nFinally, in this way they give to basic lands, the backbone of Magic, a heavier role in the game.  \n  \nSo my idea is, like the Andrea2s1's one:  \n{2}{R}  \nSorcery  \nDestroy target non-basic land  \n  \n3.5/5",
      "posted_by": "leomistico",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost184994\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">I think that land destruction should be a little slow down from Stone Rain to prevent some crazy deck type like permission and discard. Even worse you can always draw a card each turn (a new threat, a new spell to cast), but you can't recover from land destruction so easily. However I think that punish non-basic land should the way to go. The game can hinder those 300\u20ac/$ deck full of double land of some sort and give the budget (or new) player some tools to have a chance... Also a reason why the <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Primeval Titan\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Primeval Titan\">Primeval Titan</a> should read \"basic land\". Like the non-budget player weren't incentivated enough... in the same vein they could bring <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ruination\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ruination\">Ruination</a> back!<br/>Finally, in this way they give to basic lands, the backbone of Magic, a heavier role in the game.<br/><br/>So my idea is, like the Andrea2s1's one:<br/>{2}{R}<br/>Sorcery<br/>Destroy target non-basic land<br/><br/>3.5/5</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '184994'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                             